gomodel:SYNGO_1609  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" , "Rationale: In this paper, the authors raise two monoclonal antibodies against a protein of 65 000 Da molecular weight (p65 or synaptotagmin-1), which specifically label synaptic vesicle membranes in nerve terminals and are used for immunoisolation of vesicular structures with characteristics of SVs from brain homogenates. The paper represents the first report on synaptotagmin-1 identified in a screen for antibodies against SV proteins.\n\n5/2/2018 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Rat brain synaptic membranes were prepared by the procedure of Jones and\nMatus" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1542-3498" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3898-5197" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0808-7003" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1609" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

